#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:3
msgid "Harvesting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:5
msgid "The process of creating new :doc:`blocks <block>` is called harvesting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:7
msgid ""
"In this process, the :doc:`account <account>` that harvests a block is "
"called the **harvester** and is rewarded with any :doc:`transaction fees "
"<fees>` produced and any :doc:`inflation <inflation>` tokens generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:9
msgid ""
"Each produced block stores in its :ref:`header <block-header>` the public"
" key of the harvester account and the block's signature that it created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:15
msgid "Eligibility criteria"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:17
msgid ""
"The :ref:`importance score <importance-calculation>` determines the "
"probability that an account is chosen to harvest the next block among all"
" the accounts which have harvesting enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:19
msgid ""
"|codename|'s public network defines that an account needs to hold at "
"least **10,000** :ref:`harvesting mosaics <harvesting-mosaic>` to have an"
" importance score greater than zero. Eligible accounts can use their "
"importance score to create new blocks either by :ref:`running a node "
"<local-harvesting>` or enabling :ref:`delegated harvesting <delegated-"
"harvesting>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:22
msgid ""
"Regardless of the method chosen, **any account willing to activate "
"harvesting must first announce a valid** :ref:`vrfkeylinktransaction`. "
"This key is required by |codename| to randomize harvester selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:28
msgid "Harvesting mosaic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:30
msgid ""
"The |codename| platform supports :ref:`defining any mosaic <config-"
"network-properties>` for harvesting purposes to fit different business "
"needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:32
msgid ""
"For example, consortium networks can distribute harvesting mosaics "
"between the companies that are running the infrastructure, while other "
"participants need to pay fees in the form of :doc:`currency mosaic "
"<fees>` to consume services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:34
msgid ""
"By contrast, public networks might use the same mosaic for paying "
"transaction fees and running the network. |codename|'s public network "
"uses |networkcurrency| as the harvesting mosaic, enabling any eligible "
"participant to harvest new blocks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:41
msgid "Rewards"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:43
msgid ""
"Network operators can define a **network fee sink account** that will "
"receive a percentage of the harvesting rewards (block :doc:`fees <fees>` "
"and :doc:`inflation <inflation>`). In the case of the public main "
"network, this fee is set to **5%** and is used to support the different "
":doc:`reward-programs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:45
msgid ""
"Additionally, each node can set a **beneficiary account** to share a "
"percentage (up to 25%) of the harvesting rewards. The node operators can "
"use this feature to create incentive structures for their node "
"supporters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:47
msgid ""
"The sharing ratios for the beneficiary and network sink accounts are "
":ref:`configurable per network <config-network-properties>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:53
msgid ""
"Rewards division when the network's sharing ratio for network sink is 20%"
" and for beneficiary is 10%."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:55
msgid ""
"The calculation of the beneficiary percentage will occur after the "
"network sink calculation. When the node operator does not define a "
"beneficiary or a Network Fee Sink, all the rewards go to the block "
"signer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:61
msgid "Harvesting types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:63
msgid ""
"There are different kinds of harvesting available, depending on whether "
"or not the harvester account owns the node and the amount of desired "
"security: :ref:`Local <local-harvesting>`, :ref:`Remote <remote-"
"harvesting>` and :ref:`Delegated <delegated-harvesting>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:69
msgid "Local harvesting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:71
msgid ""
"This is the **simplest to set up**, and the **most insecure method**. It "
"requires changing a node's configuration, so it is only available to node"
" owners. It is enabled by filling-in the appropriate harvesting "
"properties in the :ref:`node configuration <node-properties-harvesting-"
"configuration>` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:73
msgid ""
"As it can be seen, the harvester account's **private key** is stored in "
"the ``harvesterSigningPrivateKey`` property, since it is needed to sign "
"off created blocks. This is a **security concern** since this account "
"contains funds and the configuration file might be accessed by uninvited "
"actors if the node is compromised. Funded accounts' **private keys should"
" always be stored offline**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:75
msgid ""
"Therefore, **this method is strongly discouraged**. :ref:`Remote <remote-"
"harvesting>` or :ref:`delegated <delegated-harvesting>` harvesting are "
"recommended instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:81
msgid "Remote harvesting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:83
msgid ""
"Node owners can use a **remote account** to **act as proxy** and sign off"
" the newly created blocks, while harvesting fees are still collected by "
"their main account. **The remote account has no funds**, so the fact that"
" its private key is exposed in a configuration file on the node is not a "
"concern. The :ref:`importance score <importance-calculation>` is still "
"based on the main account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:85
msgid ""
"In this setup the main account is still called the **Harvester**, for "
"simplicity, whereas the remote account is called a **Proxy**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:87
msgid ""
"Remote harvesting is enabled just like :ref:`local harvesting <local-"
"harvesting>` but using the remote account's private key in the "
"``harvesterSigningPrivateKey`` property and announcing an "
":ref:`accountkeylinktransaction` that links the remote and main accounts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:89
msgid ""
"This is the **recommended method** for node owners. See the "
":doc:`Harvesting guides <../guides/harvesting/index>` for step-by-step "
"instructions on how to activate remote harvesting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:95
msgid "Delegated harvesting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:97
msgid ""
":ref:`Eligible accounts <account_eligibility>` **not owning a node** can "
"still benefit from harvesting by **requesting a node to harvest for "
"them**. The account's :ref:`importance score <importance-calculation>` is"
" used and any collected fees are divided among the account and the node's"
" beneficiary (as explained in the :ref:`Rewards <harvesting-rewards>` "
"section). **It is a advantageous agreement to both the account and the "
"node.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:99
msgid ""
"It is then said that the account **delegates harvesting** to the node, "
"but the account is still considered the harvester."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:101
msgid ""
"Delegated harvesting is enabled similarly to :ref:`remote harvesting "
"<remote-harvesting>` but, since the account has no access to the node's "
"configuration, it announces a :ref:`PersistentDelegationRequest "
"transaction <persistentdelegationrequesttransaction>` instead (This can "
"be done effortlessly from the :ref:`Wallet <wallet-desktop>`). Upon "
"receiving the request, **the node may or may not grant it**, depending on"
" its configuration and the rest of requests received."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:103
msgid ""
"As with :ref:`remote harvesting <remote-harvesting>` a proxy remote "
"account is used so the main account's private key is never put at risk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/harvesting.rst:105
msgid ""
"See the :doc:`Harvesting guides <../guides/harvesting/index>` for step-"
"by-step instructions on how to activate delegated harvesting and check if"
" the delegation request has been granted."
msgstr ""

